title: Mastering Japanese 1
description:
Mastering Japanese (1963) - 8 cassettes (which I digitalized by way of stone knives and bearskins...) lessons 1-20  with textbook 'Beginning Japanese' by Eleanor Harz Jorden

-intensive audio programme
-complete language immersion course 
-created by the federal agency that trains U.S. government personnel in foreign language proficiency, the Foreign Service Language Institute (FSI). 

"If you want more from a language course than list of phrases for travelers, this is the program for you. This comprehensive book/cassette or CD program will help you develop total fluency in less time than you ever thought possible. 

You'll master grammar, pronunciation and vocabulary as you gain complete spoken command of the language." 

Other FSI language courses can be found at http://fsi-language-courses.com
